Aim
To write a C++ program that generates a dynamic web page using CGI (Common Gateway Interface).

⭐ Program 1: Simple C++ CGI Program (Display Webpage)
Algorithm
Start the C++ program
Print the HTTP header: Content-Type: text/html
Print HTML tags such as <html>, <body>
Print content inside the HTML
End the program

Code
Save as hello.cgi (after compiling).

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
int main() {
    cout << "Content-Type: text/html\n\n";
    cout << "<html>";
    cout << "<head><title>Welcome</title></head>";
    cout << "<body>";
    cout << "<h1>Hello from C++ Web Programming!</h1>";
    cout << "<p>This webpage is generated using a C++ CGI Program.</p>";
    cout << "</body>";
    cout << "</html>";
    return 0;
}

Output (Displayed in Browser)
Hello from C++ Web Programming!
This webpage is generated using a C++ CGI Program.

⭐ Program 2: C++ CGI Program to Read Form Input
HTML Form (save as form.html)
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>
<form action="/cgi-bin/process.cgi" method="GET">
    Enter your name: <input type="text" name="name">
    <input type="submit" value="Submit">
</form>
</body>
</html>

C++ CGI Script (process.cgi)
#include <iostream>
#include <string>
using namespace std;
int main() {
    cout << "Content-Type: text/html\n\n";

    // get data from QUERY_STRING
    string query = getenv("QUERY_STRING");

    // extract name from query: name=John
    string name = query.substr(query.find("=") + 1);
    cout << "<html><body>";
    cout << "<h2>Welcome, " << name << "!</h2>";
    cout << "<p>You entered your name through a web form.</p>";
    cout << "</body></html>";
    return 0;
}
Output (Displayed After Submitting Form)
Welcome, <name>!
You entered your name through a web form.

Result
Web programming using C++ was successfully implemented using CGI scripts to generate dynamic web pages and process form input.
